From 30ebb7954bdaf0cd7e9b7c2b309e93c0368acbf1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Karthikeya <karthi@jovio.in>
Date: Sun, 28 Jun 2026 13:10:56 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] feat(auth): /forgot-password + /reset-password flow
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- New /forgot-password page: enters email, calls supabase.auth
  .resetPasswordForEmail with redirectTo /reset-password. Generic
  success message regardless of whether account exists (prevents
  account enumeration). Surfaces rate-limit errors separately.
- New /reset-password page: handles Supabase PASSWORD_RECOVERY event,
  validates password (>=8 chars + match), calls auth.updateUser,
  redirects to /dashboard. Falls back to 'request new link' if the
  recovery session can't be established (expired link).
- Login page: added 'Forgot password?' link right under password field.

No backend / DB changes required — Supabase Auth handles the email
sending via its default template (configurable in Supabase dashboard
→ Auth → Email Templates).
